  "text": "The SharedInformer factory architecture in kubernetes/kubernetes is a complex system for managing informers that sync with the Kubernetes API server. The implementation spans multiple files and components:\n\n## Core Architecture\n\nThe SharedInformer factory is implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/informers/factory.go` with the `sharedInformerFactory` struct and `SharedInformerFactory` interface. This factory manages a collection of `SharedIndexInformer` instances, allowing multiple clients to share informers and reducing memory footprint and API server connections.\n\n## Informer Registration\n\nThe core informer registration happens through:\n- `NewSharedInformerFactory()` and `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions()` in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/informers/factory.go` - Creates the factory with default or custom resync periods\n- `sharedInformerFactory.InformerFor()` - Returns or creates informers for specific object types\n- `NewSharedIndexInformerWithOptions()` in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/shared_informer.go` - Creates individual SharedIndexInformer instances\n\nThe `SharedInformer` and `SharedIndexInformer` interfaces defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/shared_informer.go` provide the contract for event handler registration via `AddEventHandler()` and `AddEventHandlerWithResyncPeriod()` methods.\n\n## List-Watch Mechanism\n\nThe list-watch mechanism is implemented through:\n- `ListerWatcher` interface in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/listwatch.go` - Combines `Lister` and `Watcher` interfaces\n- `ListWatch` struct - Concrete implementation providing `ListFunc` and `WatchFunc` for API server communication\n- `NewFilteredListWatchFromClient()` - Creates ListWatch from Kubernetes client\n- `Reflector` in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go` - Watches API server using ListerWatcher and updates the local cache\n- `Controller` in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/controller.go` - Low-level controller managing Reflector and processing queue\n\n## Local Cache Store Sync\n\nThe local cache store sync is implemented through:\n- `DeltaFIFO` in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/delta_fifo.go` - Queue maintaining deltas (changes) to objects, with `KnownObjects` field pointing to the cache\n- `Store` and `Indexer` interfaces in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/store.go` and `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/index.go` - Abstract cache storage\n- `sharedIndexInformer.HandleDeltas()` - Processes deltas from DeltaFIFO and updates both the indexer and notifies handlers\n- `WaitForCacheSync()` and `WaitForNamedCacheSync()` - Functions to wait until informer's cache is synced with API server\n\n## Event Distribution\n\nEvent distribution to handlers is managed by:\n- `sharedProcessor` in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/shared_informer.go` - Distributes notifications to all registered listeners\n- `processorListener` - Manages individual handler's event queue with `add()`, `pop()`, and `run()` methods\n- `ResourceEventHandler` interface in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/controller.go` - Handler contract with `OnAdd()`, `OnUpdate()`, and `OnDelete()` methods\n- `ResourceEventHandlerRegistration` interface - Returned by handler registration, tracks if handler has synced\n\n## Sync Tracking\n\nSync state tracking is implemented in:\n- `synctrack/synctrack.go` with `SingleFileTracker` and `AsyncTracker` - Track when handlers have processed all initial items\n- `processorListener.HasSynced()` - Reports if handler has synced\n- `sharedIndexInformer.HasSynced()` - Reports if informer has synced with API server\n\n## Code Generation\n\nThe informer factory and type-specific informers are generated by:\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/informer-gen/generators/factory.go` - Code generator templates for factory\n- Templates generate concrete informers for each API type (e.g., `DeploymentInformer`, `PodInformer`) in `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/informers/*/`\n\n## Thread Safety\n\nThread safety is ensured through:\n- `sharedInformerFactory.lock` (sync.Mutex) - Protects factory's informer map\n- `sharedIndexInformer.startedLock` - Protects start/stop state\n- `sharedIndexInformer.blockDeltas` - Synchronizes handler registration with event distribution\n- `sharedProcessor.listenersLock` - Protects listener map\n- `DeltaFIFO.lock` - Protects queue state\n- `thread_safe_store.go` - Provides thread-safe store implementation"
